Chinese Returning from Fighting with ISIS in Syria Arrested - Latest News Briefs - Arutz Sheva
The top Communist official in China's Xinjiang region said Tuesday that extremists from the mainly Muslim region have been apprehended after returning from fighting in Syria with the Islamic State. Zhang Chunxian, party head in Xinjiang, told reporters that the radicals were caught when a terror plot was recently uncovered, reported the Global Times, which is affiliated with the ruling party mouthpiece People's Daily.
He said that they had returned to Xinjiang, the homeland of China's Uighur ethnic minority, to participate in violent terror plots, the report said. But heapparently gave no details, including the number of people apprehended. Other Chinese media carried similar reports, but did not specifically mention Syria.